## Best Practices

### When to Use Details

Use collapsible sections for:
- ✅ Supplementary information
- ✅ Optional content
- ✅ Code examples
- ✅ FAQ items
- ✅ Technical details

Don't use for:
- ❌ Critical content (might be missed)
- ❌ Very short content (not worth collapsing)
- ❌ Information needed for context

### Accessibility

:::details [Accessibility Note]
Collapsible sections should:
- Have clear, descriptive titles
- Be keyboard navigable
- Screen reader friendly
- Remember user's expand/collapse state
:::

